			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Last night I was asked to attend a 'Loyalist faction raid' out in Dranik's Scar. Seeing as I was just barely apprehensive to these mobs earlier that day, I figured 'why not,' and went for it. Approximately 2 hours later, I found that I was amiable. Never even saw indifferent. And seeing how I've spent the past week at dubious, I was ecstatic that this worked so well.
<br />
All we did was grab 2 pullers and some people with AoEs. Have the pullers go in a cycle, one rounding up mobs and another killing a group with the main raid force. Each puller would bring in anywhere from 5 to 12 mobs at a time, and all of 'em would get chewed up by our AoEs, pets by the time the second puller arrived with their group of mobs. Rinse, repeat... clear entire zone if ya want.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
